 Arts Council All Rights Reserved About the Council Members The appointed California Arts Council consists of eleven members who serve four year staggered terms The Governor appoints nine members the Legislature appoints two members Council Members serve without salary elect their own chair and meet throughout the state to encourage public attendance This body has final approval of California Arts Council grants and contracts California Arts Council Members Barbara George Chair California Arts Council Chairperson 2002 Vice Chairperson for Northern California 1999 2002 Arts Council member since 1994 Member Public Art Selection panel for proposed Caltrans building in Los Angeles Chairperson of the Arts Committee State of California San Francisco Civic Center Complex Past member of the Docent Council for the http www thinker org Fine Arts Museums of San Francisco Trustee California State Summer School for the Arts CSSSA Board of Directors Judicial Family Institute Art Consultant Junipero Serra State Office Building Los Angeles Partner George Jacobson Interiors 1968 1995 member several councils of art museums in California She was first appointed by Governor Pete Wilson in 1994 On March 3 1999 Governor Gray Davis appointed George to a second term on the Council and she was confirmed unanimously by the State Senate On February 27 2003 Governor Davis reappointed her to the Council Her term expires on January 1 2007 Phyllis F Epstein Vice Chair of La Jolla has served as chair for the San Diego Center for Jewish Culture at the Lawrence Family Jewish Community Center since 1994 In this position she helps coordinate the Jewish Film Festival the http www lfjcc org streisand html Streisand Festival of New Jewish Plays the Jewish Book Fair and the Children s Theatre Group She also has served as chair of the Cultural Arts Committee at Congregation Beth Israel in 1997 Previously she was a member of the board of directors of the Museum of Photographic Arts Epstein earned a bachelor of arts degree from the University of California Los Angeles Epstein was appointed by Governor Gray Davis on December 9 1999 to a four year term On February 27 2003 Governor Davis reappointed her to the Council Her term expires on January 1 2007 Marcy Friedman Vice Chair of Sacramento is a design consultant for Art Design of Sacramento Her work includes many of the shopping centers in the Sacramento area Friedman has more than 35 years of experience in the arts community including non profit board service She is a member of the http www sacculture com Sacramento Metropolitan Arts Commission the http www crockerartmuseum org Crocker Art Museum where she serves as trustee and president and the Sacramento Regional Foundation As a member of the Sacramento Metropolitan Arts Commission she serves on the Art in Public Places Committee and was actively involved in selecting the public artworks that beautify Sacramento s newest airport terminal She earned a Bachelor of Arts degree from Stanford University Governor Gray Davis appointed Friedman on January 31 2000 to a three year term On February 27 2003 Governor Davis reappointed her to the Council Her term expires on January 1 2007 Robert J Abernethy of Los Angeles is a real estate developer and President of American Standard Development Company and Self Storage Management Company Abernethy received a B A in mathematics and electrical engineering from Johns Hopkins and a MBA from Harvard Business School His many accomplishments include assistant to chief scientist for the Phoenix missile program at Hughes Aircraft Co Los Angeles as well as serving as the director of the Los Angeles MTA for three years He is a member of the advisory board of the Peabody Conservatory as well as a trustee of the Johns Hopkins University He is also a member of the California State Board of Education as well as a former member of the California Transportation Commission He is on the Council on Foreign Relations and the Pacific Council on International Policy Since 1980 he has been a member of the Board of Directors of Public Storage Inc Assembly Speaker Robert Hertzberg appointed him on January 31 2000 to a term that expires on January 1 2004 Aurelia Mika Chang of Sacramento is a concert pianist She began her piano studies at the age of six and made her debut with the New Jersey Symphony Orchestra at the age of 16 Since then Ms Chang has made solo orchestral and chamber appearances in the United States Austria Germany Poland Japan and China She has won top honors in several competitions including the New Jersey Symphony Orchestra s Young Artist Auditions Juilliard s Therese Kleppel Prize and Juilliard s Concerto Competition Ms Chang recently performed at Suntory Hall chamber music concerts with members of the Philadelphia Orchestra Beijing Concert Hall LeFrak Concert Hall Aaron Copland School of Music New York Alice Tully Hall Lincoln Center New York Chopin Society and Shanghai Concert Hall She earned bachelor and master of music in piano degrees from the Juilliard School of Music Governor Gray Davis appointed Chang on December 19 2001 her term expires in January 1 2005 Janet Dreisen a native of Los Angeles is a founder of the http www moca la org museum Museum of Contemporary Art MOCA and serves as a member of the Board of Trustees of the California Institute of the Arts She sits on the boards of the Rape Treatment Center of Santa Monica UCLA Hospital the L A Conservation Corporation the Archives of American Art Blue Ribbon of the LA Music Center and the International Directors Council of the Guggenheim Museum in New York City She was recently appointed to the Advisory Board of the Annenberg School of Communication at the University of Southern California She was appointed by the State Senate in March 1997 and reappointed in April 2000 her term expires in 2004 Steven J Fogel of Los Angeles is the co founder and Chief Executive Officer of Westwood Financial Corporation a real estate investment firm established in 1970 He is also an oil color artist whose works have been placed in several public exhibitions as well as a published author Fogel earned a bachelor of science degree from the University of Southern California Governor Gray Davis first appointed Fogel on April 16 1999 his term expires on January 1 2006 Dr Jerrold Hiura of Los Gatos has been a dentist with Hiura and Hiura Inc of San Jose since 1976 He is immediate past Chair for the Arts Council Silicon Valley and past Chair of the San Jose Arts Commission Dr Hiura is an artist whose work in costume jewelry design led to several lacquerware collections that were used to accessorize fashion shows featuring Geoffrey Beene Bill Blass and Kenzo Dr Hiura founded in 1994 the Contemporary Asian Theater Scene CATS a nonprofit producer presenter of Asian American theater productions He earned a bachelor of arts degree from the University of California Berkeley and a D D S degree from Washington University Governor Gray Davis appointed Hiura on December 20 2002 his term expires on January 1 2006 Michael Rubel of Los Angeles is general counsel at Creative Artists Agency CAA a talent and literary agency that represents many of the world s most important artists in film television and music From 1976 to 1997 he was a corporate lawyer in private practice in Los Angeles Following his 1984 to 1989 tenure as Managing Partner at Dern Mason Floum Mr Rubel served as Managing Partner at Del Rubel Shaw Mason Derin from 1989 to 1997 He earned bachelor and master of arts degrees from Brown University and a juris doctorate degree from UCLA Governor Gray Davis appointed Rubel on December 20 2002 his term expires on January 1 2005 
